text:
Jacobus Place, north from Leyden Street (where it commences), to its point of termination where Van Corlear Place turns off to the left, and Fort Charles Place to the right. The 2 -story frame houses, at the apex are (left) No. 1 Van Corlear Place and (right) No. 1 Fort Charles Place.

October 26, 1927.

P. L. Sperr.

original_title: Manhattan: Fort Charles Place - Jacobus Place
text:
Fort Charles Place, north from Jacobus Place to Marble Hill Avenue, showing the repaving of this thoroughfare by the Works Progress Administration. This series of photos is progressive.

May 3, 1937
1-2-3

W. P. A., photo
